><td char="." align="char">32</td><td align="left">100&#x000a0;&#x000d7;&#x000a0;30/32</td></tr><tr><td char="." align="char">96.66&#x000a0;%</td><td align="left"/><td char="." align="char">100&#x000a0;%</td><td align="left"/><td char="." align="char">93.75&#x000a0;%</td></tr></tbody></table><table-wrap-foot><p>Relative accuracy, sensitivity and specificity were calculated as follows: accuracy AC&#x000a0;=&#x000a0;((PA&#x000a0;+&#x000a0;NA)/<italic>N</italic>)&#x000a0;&#x000d7;&#x000a0;100&#x000a0;%; specificity SP&#x000a0;=&#x000a0;(NA/<italic>N</italic>)&#x000a0;&#x000d7;&#x000a0;100&#x000a0;%; sensitivity: SE&#x000a0;=&#x000a0;(PA/<italic>N</italic>)&#x000a0;&#x000d7;&#x000a0;100&#x000a0;%, where PA is the agreement for positive results; NA is the agreement for negative results; <italic>N</italic> is the total number of samples; <italic>N</italic>
